After comparing those sequences with germline database, 10 germline HCs and 11 germline LCs was used (Table 2
). IGHV1–69 (5/19) and IGHV3–23 (5/19) are the major germline HC whereas IGLV7–43 is the major germline LC (Fig. 1
A and B). As IGHV1–69 was the highest HC germline used in our anti-DENV HuMAbs, interestingly, the highest percentage of IGHV1–69 HC germline was also previously reported from other anti-viral MAbs, such as influenza virus [14], [19], HIV, SARS CoV, Hendra, and Nipah virus [16].

To study the function of isolated VH and VL, those 3 best HuMAbs were selected for production of rIgG, by subcloning of variable region of HC and LC to another 2 mammalian expression plasmids containing either constant HC or constant LC (kappa or lambda). The constructed plasmids were co-transfected to human embryonated kidney (HEK) 293T cell for rIgG expression, for testing of both binding and neutralizing activity. All three clones can bind to 4 serotypes of dengue virus infected Vero cell with the same manner as IgG secreted from hybridoma cell (Fig. 2
). Moreover, three of them also show almost the same neutralizing activity as those from hybridomas (Fig. 3
).
